Question: Which five teams average the most points per game?
GPT Generated SQL:
SELECT team_name, (team_points / CAST(games AS FLOAT)) AS average_points_per_game
FROM team
ORDER BY average_points_per_game DESC
LIMIT 5;
Reponse Interpreted by GPT: The five teams that average the most points per game are Alabama with 90.89, Kentucky with 89.17, Gonzaga with 88.4, Iowa with 86.75, and South Dakota with 86.62.

Question: Which player averages the most points per game?
GPT Generated SQL:
SELECT first_name, last_name, (total_points * 1.0 / games_played) AS points_per_game
FROM player
ORDER BY points_per_game DESC
LIMIT 1;
Reponse Interpreted by GPT: Elijah Foster averages the most points per game, with an average of 19.55 points per game.

Question: What player averages the most steals per game?
GPT Generated SQL:
SELECT p.first_name, p.last_name, (t.steals / CAST(t.games AS FLOAT)) AS steals_per_game
FROM player p
JOIN team t ON p.team_id = t.team_id
ORDER BY steals_per_game DESC
LIMIT 1;
Reponse Interpreted by GPT: The player Simas Lukosius averages the most steals per game with an average of 8.722.

Question: Which Big12 team has the best average margin of victory?
GPT Generated SQL:
SELECT team_name, (AVG(team_points) - AVG(opponent_points)) AS avg_margin_victory
FROM team
JOIN conference ON team.conference_id = conference.conference_id
WHERE conference.conference_name = 'Big12'
GROUP BY team.team_id
ORDER BY avg_margin_victory DESC
LIMIT 1;

Question: Which Big 12 team has the best average margin of victory?
GPT Generated SQL:
SELECT t.team_name, 
       AVG((t.team_points - t.opponent_points) / t.games) AS average_margin_of_victory
FROM team t
JOIN conference c ON t.conference_id = c.conference_id
WHERE c.conference_name = 'Big 12'
GROUP BY t.team_id
ORDER BY average_margin_of_victory DESC
LIMIT 1;
Reponse Interpreted by GPT: The Big 12 team with the best average margin of victory is Houston, with an average margin of 21.0 points.
